systems in Budapest and Paris.

00:39:02.266 --> 00:39:04.390
To be honest, he had been
spending most of his time

00:39:04.390 --> 00:39:05.560
thinking about electricity.

00:39:05.560 --> 00:39:09.650
And in the Budapest park,
envisioned the engine.

00:39:09.650 --> 00:39:14.890
But he had done such a great job
that his supervisors sent him

00:39:14.890 --> 00:39:18.520
to New York to actually work
with Thomas Edison himself.

00:39:18.520 --> 00:39:20.680
And they sent him
with, probably,

00:39:20.680 --> 00:39:23.770
the greatest letter
of recommendation

00:39:23.770 --> 00:39:25.210
that's ever been written.

00:39:25.210 --> 00:39:28.250
They said to Thomas Edison,
this letter to Thomas Edison,

00:39:28.250 --> 00:39:30.040
I know of two great men.

00:39:30.040 --> 00:39:33.940
You are one of them and
this young man is the other.

00:39:33.940 --> 00:39:37.390
So they worked
together, actually.

00:39:37.390 --> 00:39:41.380
But I mean, they were totally
different temperaments.

00:39:41.380 --> 00:39:44.200
I mean, Edison was frumpy.

00:39:44.200 --> 00:39:45.350
He was crass.

00:39:45.350 --> 00:39:46.350
I mean, he was a genius.

00:39:46.350 --> 00:39:48.183
I'm not-- you know,
there's no knocking him.

00:39:48.183 --> 00:39:49.390
He just sort of was.

00:39:49.390 --> 00:39:56.260
Tesla was this immaculately
refined cosmopolitan

00:39:56.260 --> 00:40:01.090
that spoke eight languages, knew
literature fluently, and looked

00:40:01.090 --> 00:40:04.090
like he dressed like he was
ready to go to the opera

00:40:04.090 --> 00:40:05.899
during the day.

00:40:05.899 --> 00:40:06.940
So the two of them just--

00:40:06.940 --> 00:40:08.564
they were different
sort of characters.

00:40:08.564 --> 00:40:12.772
And they argued vehemently
about how to transmit power.

00:40:12.772 --> 00:40:14.980
I mean, Edison wanted to do
it through direct current

00:40:14.980 --> 00:40:18.310
because he thought it
was, number one, his.

00:40:18.310 --> 00:40:20.740
And safer was his
biggest argument.

00:40:20.740 --> 00:40:23.470
And Tesla was far more
interested in trying

00:40:23.470 --> 00:40:25.600
to send it long distances
so that more people

00:40:25.600 --> 00:40:27.790
could take advantage of it.

00:40:27.790 --> 00:40:30.340
And in fact-- this is
more than your question

00:40:30.340 --> 00:40:37.450
was-- but they split
because Edison refused

00:40:37.450 --> 00:40:43.180
to provide the promised
bonus if Tesla would increase

00:40:43.180 --> 00:40:46.630
the efficiency of one of
the dynamos, or generators.

00:40:46.630 --> 00:40:49.390
And Tesla had worked
like three months

00:40:49.390 --> 00:40:51.710
to triple the output
of this thing.

00:40:51.710 --> 00:40:54.040
Then he goes to the Wizard
of Menlo Park, who he still

00:40:54.040 --> 00:40:58.000
idolized at this time,
and Edison basically

00:40:58.000 --> 00:40:59.260
just mocked him.

00:40:59.260 --> 00:41:02.500
And said, oh come
on, that was a joke.

00:41:02.500 --> 00:41:03.876
And then, to this
young immigrant

00:41:03.876 --> 00:41:06.250
who is still a little sensitive
about being in the United

00:41:06.250 --> 00:41:08.392
States, he says, you're
such an immigrant.

00:41:08.392 --> 00:41:09.850
If you were only
an American, you'd

00:41:09.850 --> 00:41:12.280
appreciate an American joke.

00:41:12.280 --> 00:41:14.290
[? Edison ?] of
course, did not laugh.

00:41:14.290 --> 00:41:16.620
He put on his bowler
hat, appropriately so,

00:41:16.620 --> 00:41:18.160
and walked out and quit his job.

00:41:18.160 --> 00:41:19.730
And started his own company.

00:41:19.730 --> 00:41:21.600
So that's how he got
to United States.

